snippet.title: The Devil Wears Prada 2 | Teaser Trailer
snippet.description:
A sequel? For spring? Groundbreaking. Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt, and Stanley Tucci return in The Devil Wears Prada 2, in theaters May 1, 2026. Watch the teaser trailer now. 

Almost twenty years after making their iconic turns as Miranda, Andy, Emily and Nigel—Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt and Stanley Tucci return to the fashionable streets of New York City and the sleek offices of Runway Magazine in the eagerly awaited sequel to the 2006 phenomenon that defined a generation. 
 
The film reunites the original main cast with director David Frankel and writer Aline Brosh McKenna, and introduces an all-new runway of characters including Kenneth Branagh, Simone Ashley, Justin Theroux, Lucy Liu, Patrick Brammall, Caleb Hearon, Helen J. Shen, Pauline Chalamet, B.J. Novak and Conrad Ricamora. Tracie Thoms and Tibor Feldman also reprise their roles as “Lily” and “Irv” from the first film. 
 
“The Devil Wears Prada 2” is produced by Wendy Finerman, and executive produced by Michael Bederman, Karen Rosenfelt and McKenna. The film debuts exclusively in theaters May 1, 2026.

snippet.title: "Wuthering Heights" | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Inspired by the greatest love story of all time. “Wuthering Heights” only in theaters this Valentine’s Day. #WutheringHeightsMovie

Pre-order Charli xcx's new album "Wuthering Heights": https://wutheringheights.charlixcx.com/

From Warner Bros. Pictures and Academy Award and BAFTA-winning filmmaker Emerald Fennell comes “WUTHERING HEIGHTS,” starring Academy Award and BAFTA nominee Margot Robbie opposite BAFTA nominee Jacob Elordi.

A bold and original imagining of one of the greatest love stories of all time, Emerald Fennell’s “WUTHERING HEIGHTS” stars Margot Robbie as Cathy and Jacob Elordi as Heathcliff, whose forbidden passion for one another turns from romantic to intoxicating in an epic tale of lust, love and madness.

The film also stars alongside Oscar nominee Hong Chau, Shazad Latif, Alison Oliver, BAFTA winner Martin Clunes and Ewan Mitchell.

Fennell directs from her own screenplay, and produces alongside Oscar nominee and BAFTA award winner Josey McNamara and Robbie. Oscar nominee Tom Ackerley and Sara Desmond are executive producing.

Behind the scenes, Fennell worked with such frequent collaborators as Oscar- and BAFTA-winning director of photography Linus Sandgren, Oscar- and BAFTA-nominated production designer Suzie Davies, BAFTA-nominated editor Victoria Boydell, award-winning casting director Kharmel Cochrane and BAFTA-nominated composer Anthony Willis. Oscar and BAFTA winner Jacqueline Durran designed the costumes. Original songs by Charli XCX.

Warner Bros. Pictures and MRC Present A Lie Still & LuckyChap Entertainment Production, a film by Emerald Fennell, “WUTHERING HEIGHTS.” Distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures, the film will be in theaters nationwide on February 13, 2026, and internationally beginning 11 February.

snippet.title: Taylor Swift | The End of an Era | Official Trailer | Disney+
snippet.description:

snippet.title: FOREVER: The Full Version【Official MV】by AJ
snippet.description:
Spotify pre-save: https://distrokid.com/hyperfollow/ajdispirito/forever-the-full-version
Murder Drones vinyl!: https://glitchproductions.store/products/murder-drones-vinyl-record-3

Music, vocals, lyrics, and the entire video made by AJ
Cover Art made by Liam Vickers

Cyn model made by MONYA: https://www.youtube.com/@MonyaPlay
Tessa model made by SG_Animations https://x.com/SG_Animations
Really appreciate ya'll for making these awesome models I was able to use! 

This was my first time fully diving into 3D animation on my own. I pretty much improvised a production pipeline based on what I wanted to do lol 
This video was primarily made in Blender, with final editing done in Davinchi with some After Effects additions. I've played with Blender before, but this time I spent months learning everything I needed to (thank god for tutorials) 
I started the idea with a temp version of the main Murder Drones map Liam gave me, basically what they used in the animatics. 
With this I wanted to go for a silhouette style look with the video, as the map had no textures. 
That's where the idea to use Tessa came in, as she already had that look. I gave Cyn the same look to match the overall style. 
I then made the whole other map with the trees and tombstones, with assets from Superhive. 
The Cyn model already had a rig 🙏, but the Tessa model I had to rig on my own. 
Rigging sucks I hate it lol 
Then there came motion capture; I was able to get a Rokoko suit to do all my silly dances and stuff. 
Re-targetting mocap to a character rig was a nightmare, but somehow I made it work 🥲 
With all of the animations on the characters, it was finally time to form the scenes. 
Setting up the camera shots and actually forming the video was the best part for sure. 
So many keyframes controlling the lights, the sky, the cameras, the snow, and animation tweaks. 
I could use a slice of pizza right now 
The whole Tessa sequence was printed onto VHS and recorded back onto my computer. 

There was a lot of other things I tried to do but couldn't pull off... it happens. I learned a whole lot and I'm excited to do this again. 
If you made it this far and have any other questions on how I made anything in the video, ask in the comments!

snippet.title: Fuerza Regida - ANSIEDAD (Letra)
snippet.description:
🎵 Fuerza Regida - ANSIEDAD (Letra)

🎤Letra: ANSIEDAD

[Verso 1]
Otra vez otra en mi cama, qué puta ansiedad
Suena el timbre y tú en mi celular
Vieras qué agüite me da contestar
Tú no me entiendes ni me entenderás
Otra vez con pleitos, deja de pelear
Todo lo que hago es por ti nomás
Sabes que te amo, tú eres la especial
Las otras capillas pa' un rato nomás

[Coro]
Pero entiéndeme, mija, es la vida de artista
Me la navego ente loquera, desvergue de güeras
Y nomás la ansiedad no se va

[Interludio]
Válgame, Dios
Fuerza Regida
¿Cómo puedo, mija?

[Verso 2]
Otra vez llorando en el espejo tu vanidad
Nuevamente, concluimos, me quieres cambiar
La historia nunca va a acabar

[Coro]
Pero entiéndeme, mija, es la vida de artista
Me la navego ente loquera, desvergue de güeras
Y nomás la ansiedad no se va (Jaja)

[Outro Instrumental]

#ANSIEDAD #FuerzaRegida #Letra #VersoMexicano
